Starting with Complete Heal. It's unbalanced. Clerics shouldn't have it in the first place. The day VI decides to give an unbalancing skill to ANOTHER class, which would double if not more the number of people carrying that skill, is the day I quit EQ.<br>
As for Mana Burn. It's a powerful ability that Wizards have earned. I think Druids are competent when it comes to Direct Damage. That's just my opinion of course, and you can challenge me otherwise. The true problem lies in Healing power for Druids.<br>
Druids do need an upgrade in healing, but don't go as far as to simply resort to Complete Heal because you can't create a reasonable request.<br>
The point that druids have life quite possibly the easiest of all classes Pre-40ish is very valid. Clerics Pre-Complete Heal don't have much to offer. Our Stun and Direct Damage line of spells hasn't matured much at this point, and we have very little to offer that a Druid doesn't. Clerics clearly shine after level 39, and Druids step out of the spotlight when it comes to healing, as it should be.<br>
Whatever balance ideas are thought out and toyed with is fine by me, as long as it doesn't displace Clerics from being the best Healers in the game, hands down. I don't care if Shamans or Druids are the second best, Druids and Shamans can fight for that right, it's not my business.<br>
You want to be more useful in raids at healing? More power to you. But if you want to replace a Cleric with equal healing power, you won't be winning over much clerical support.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fyyrlustorm>FyyrLuStorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Small Pissed Off Diety<br>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333399>(7/10/02 2:28:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> &quot;So, you'd prefer arrogance, incorrect answers and brush-offs? Weird.&quot;<br>
