This is your brain (a_druid_00), this your brain on crack (Huzurdadi) <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6318"><img src="http://www3.sympatico.ca/lchisholm/luth_sig.jpg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukiruseverlifeofkarana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kirus Everlife of Karana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333399>(7/10/02 2:39:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CH and Manaburn</span><hr size=1> That's precisely the point. You put it less time then because it was easier for you. I bet a Cleric leveling along side you at an equal pace and playing time would level noticeable slower during that time, therefore making it harder for us to get there, but not you. Once we hit 39, we tend to find groups more and experience is a bit easier to obtain. While druids may find it harder, balance shifts with levels. I don't agree with it, but it's the fact of the matter.<br>
