A druid complete heal costing 800 mana would still make the druid only half the healer a cleric is. One costing 600 mana would make the druid only 66% the healer a cleric is. Either way a cleric would still be the hands down best healer in the game (not to mention buffs and resses). <p><font size="+1"><i><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="-1"><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=153420>Talyena Trueheart</a>, Hierophant of Tunare<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=203026>Tresha Trueheart</a>, Warlord for Erollisi Marr<br>Dawntreaders, Terris-Thule</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uverylowsodium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VERY LOW SODIUM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333399>(7/10/02 2:43:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Uh oh... I'm bored again</span><hr size=1> Sitting at the bar, sipping a bleeding brain in attempt to ease the aching from a newly broken toe, the priest of the woods grimaced and said for the 14th time tonight, &quot;Not at all. It'll heal. They always do.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Awfully sporting of you,&quot; proclaimed the dancer, turning back to the conga line; at the same squarely stepping on another of the druid's toes... the resulting crack more than just another broken toe, the reverberations extending into the very depth of the priest's unconscious mind.<br>
<br>
A quirky smile. A mad gleam. And... and... Fruitcake! <br>
<br>
Reaching for a bag next to the barstool, a pair of clogs emerging, the druid proclaimed loudly, &quot;It is time to go dancing!&quot;<br>
<br>
And dance the treehugger did, leaving swearing masses holding their toes behind. Looking about, other druids were seen prancing madly about the dance floor. And in the center, in his polyester whites, Adion, a very short and angry Fred Astaire, his feet seeming never to touch the floor... tapping about from toe to toe.<br>
<br>
A cry, once dim and distant, grew loud as clog clad druids, mass hysteria, spread across Norrath. And somewhere, mad eyed, huddled in the ruins of his temple, a cleric whispered, &quot;Let them eat fruitcake.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uislington.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Islington</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333399>(7/10/02 2:46:42 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CH and Manaburn</span><hr size=1> Huzurdadi, that is pure paranoia and biased talk that you're spewing right now.  You just CAN'T accept that one of the evil Clerics might actually agree with PRIESTS needing upgrades.  I say Priests and I mean it.  As we have FINALLY established, this whole thread is NOT about Druids but about all Healing classes in general (or rather that is what this thread has become).<br>
<br>
Yes I left blanks in my ideas.  I am NOT a game designer nor do I play one on TV.  I'm simply more concerned about BALANCE while you are more concerned about making a Druid SUPER class.<br>
<br>
FINE, you want numbers, here are some EXAMPLES of what I meant.  These are NOT set in stone but a mere example of what I meant by my ideas for fixing Priest classes.<br>
<br>
Clerics get a 2400 point heal for 600 mana.  4 points of health for 1 point of mana.  5 second cast time and no recast (other than the inherant 2.5 seconds).<br>
<br>
Give Druids a 2000 point heal for 571 mana.  3.5 points of health for 1 point of mana.  That is still MILES above Natures Touch.  6 second cast time and a 5 second recast (plus the inherant 2.5 seconds).<br>
<br>
As far as lower level Druids go, you're getting Natures Touch moved down to Level 57 by way of this upgrade.  Seems like this will address pre 60 problems to me as you now have a fast cast heal and a big punch heal up until 60 when you get a bigger punch heal.  Don't see where I am ignoring less than level 60 Priests.<br>
<br>
